<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8"/>
<title>Ch 2 What marketing is · 20 · Closing · The diagnostic</title>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="../_tokens.css"/>
<style>
  .slide.closing{ display:flex; flex-direction:column; }
  .closing .head{ margin-bottom:20px; }
  .closing .grid{
    display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1fr;
    gap:34px; flex:1; min-height:0; align-items:start;
  }
  .closing .takeaways{ display:flex; flex-direction:column; gap:6px; }
  .closing .t{
    display:grid; grid-template-columns: 32px 1fr; gap:14px; align-items:baseline;
    padding:11px 0; border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .closing .t:last-child{ border-bottom:none; }
  .closing .t .n{
    font-size:22px; font-weight:600; color:var(--accent); letter-spacing:-0.01em;
  }
  .closing .t .txt{ font-size:20px; line-height:1.34; color:var(--ink-body); }
  .closing .t .txt strong{ color:var(--ink); font-weight:600; }

  .closing .aside{
    background:var(--bg-soft);
    padding:24px 26px; display:flex; flex-direction:column; justify-content:space-between;
  }
  .closing .aside h4{
    font-size:11px; font-weight:600; letter-spacing:0.14em; text-transform:uppercase;
    color:var(--ink-mute); margin-bottom:14px;
  }
  .closing .aside .preview{
    font-size:26px; font-weight:500; line-height:1.25; color:var(--ink);
  }
  .closing .aside .preview em{ font-style:italic; color:var(--accent); font-weight:500; }
  .closing .aside .when{
    font-size:13px; color:var(--ink-label); letter-spacing:0.04em;
    margin-top:22px; padding-top:14px; border-top:1px solid var(--rule);
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>
  <!-- 20 · CLOSING / TAKEAWAYS · the four-step diagnostic. ONE coral element = the step numbers. -->
  <section class="slide closing">
    <div class="head">
      <h1 class="title">Run the four-step read on <em>a brand you actually buy</em>.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid">
      <div class="takeaways">
        <div class="t">
          <span class="n">01</span>
          <span class="txt"><strong>Fill the five slots.</strong> One plain line each for what, who, what to charge, where, and how.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="t">
          <span class="n">02</span>
          <span class="txt"><strong>Name the binding decision.</strong> Targeting usually sets the other four behind it.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="t">
          <span class="n">03</span>
          <span class="txt"><strong>Hunt for the contradiction.</strong> Find the one slot that points somewhere the others do not.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="t">
          <span class="n">04</span>
          <span class="txt"><strong>Score the coherence.</strong> If all five point at one buyer, the brand holds; hand the lines to a saved AI workspace to grade.</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="aside">
        <div>
          <h4>Next chapter</h4>
          <p class="preview">Ch. 3 &mdash; <em>The marketing environment</em>: this chapter held the world still; now buyers change and the floor shifts.</p>
        </div>
        <p class="when">Patagonia ran the read and held; Bud Light did not and broke. The machinery is enough to judge any brand's five decisions today.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="source">MKTG 4333 · Chapter 2 · What Marketing Is</p>
  </section>
</body>
</html>
